I have never had such a disgusting experience in my life. On Friday night me, two of my roommates and 2 out-of-town guests visited the Iowa City pancheros location. The first thing we noticed when entering the store was the blaring music being played by the employees. The entrance was cramped and we stood at the door for a moment trying to figure out how to properly distance from other customers. The second we started entering the store and paused a few members of the employees started yelling at us to stand on the dots. It was hard to hear them because of the music and they were very rude about it. When through the music we were finally able to process what they were saying we tried to follow directions the best we were able and I tried to explain to my friend that has never been to a pancheros how the menu worked. We were socially distanced from any other customer besides our own group which is usually OK in any other restaurant I visited. But very quickly after we tried to talk amongst ourselves 2 employees came from behind the counter and very rudely started yelling at us and try to usher us to individual little dots by ourselves so we couldn’t speak to each other. It felt like we were being herded like cattle. When I finally got to the counter I could barely even hear my own thoughts let alone the employee trying to take my order. Luckily I already knew my order so I was able to manage but it was much harder for my friend behind me. The second I was done with my transaction I left the store very angry and anxious. Another member of my group was still in there finishing up their transaction and told us that once the first of us left they started saying rude things about us. On top of all that one of the employees wasn’t even wearing a mask. It wasn’t about our safety it was about finding ways to get away with bullying customers. Our friend thought the food was good but he still never wants to visit Pancheros again because of this experience. I feel disgusted I feel violated. From the loud music, to the constant yelling, to the rude words behind our back, to the not caring about our safety by not wearing masks while handling food, I feel ashamed for your restaurant. I try to be understanding because I worked in food service before and understand some of the pressures but the way the employees acted was honestly deplorable. I’ve been trying to contact pancheros and the store personally to no answer.

I continue to be impressed by Pancheros. Made-to-order tortillas - pressed and grilled before your eyes is the restaurant's highlight, and bring the menu to life. There is simply nothing that compares to a hot-of-the-grill, soft-yet-crispy tortilla to surround the delicious selections of meats, veggies, and salsas, which by the way are "bobbed" (mixed around with a small spoon-like device) before the burrito is wrapped - evenly distributing the ingredients around so every bite features all of your selections. If you're in the mood for fast-casual burritos, you must give Pancheros a shot if you haven't already. I prefer Pancheros over Chipotle, QDoba, Moe's, etc. - the fresh tortilla is simply sublime.
